# Patch 0029 — Kavacha SDK + plugin permission model + about:plugins (ROADMAP
# Phase 3 "Kavacha SDK + plugin permission model"; ADR 0011).
#
# WHAT: a permissioned plugin platform. sdk/kavacha-plugin.schema.json defines
# the kavacha-plugin.json manifest; KavachaPluginPermissions.sys.mjs owns the
# four grantable capabilities (workspaces / tabs / notes / commands) and
# persists per-plugin, user-granted permissions to profile
# kavacha-plugins/grants.json; KavachaSDK.sys.mjs is the capability facade a
# plugin calls — every method is gated on the plugin's live grants, and it
# exposes workspaces/tabs/notes/commands ONLY (read + safe-create workspaces,
# http/https/about tabs on the active window, the current workspace note, and
# Cmd+K command registration). KavachaPluginManager.sys.mjs is a process
# singleton that sideloads plugins from profile kavacha-plugins/<id>/, activates
# the enabled+granted ones with a least-privilege SDK, and drives the lifecycle
# (enable/disable/grant/uninstall). about:plugins — a JS nsIAboutModule exactly
# like about:studio (ADR 0009) — is the management page: list installed plugins,
# grant/revoke each declared permission, enable/disable, uninstall.
#
# WHY: plugins must extend Kavacha without ever reaching passwords, saved
# credentials, autofill, browsing history, or chrome internals. That exclusion
# is STRUCTURAL — the grantable permission enum has no value for private data,
# and there is no SDK method that could reach it — not a policy toggle. Runtime
# commands dogfood the patch-0027 registry: each plugin command carries a
# literal rawLabel + an identity l10nId + a capability, registered with
# source="plugin:<id>" so disabling a plugin drops every command it added via
# unregisterBySource. Plugins are sideloaded (offline) for now; remote install
# via the marketplace (patch 0028) is a later integration. A real JS
# sandbox/compartment isolation boundary per plugin is a hardening follow-up —
# today granted plugins are trusted-on-grant and the SDK is the only sanctioned
# surface.
#
# NOT BUILD-VERIFIED: authored against the post-0028 tree; run
# `git -C browser/zen-upstream apply --check` + a Marionette pass (sideload a
# plugin under profile kavacha-plugins/<id>/, open about:plugins, grant a
# permission and enable, watch its command reach Cmd+K, disable and watch it
# leave, revoke, uninstall) before marking the ROADMAP item verified. The
# manifest schema + SDK reference (sdk/kavacha-plugin.schema.json, sdk/README.md)
# live as repo-level design files — like customization/**/*.schema.json — and are
# NOT part of this overlay patch. This patch adds
# src/zen/common/sys/KavachaPluginManager.sys.mjs, KavachaPluginPermissions.sys.mjs,
# KavachaSDK.sys.mjs, and src/zen/kavacha-plugins/* (about:plugins); touches
# src/zen/common/modules/ZenStartup.mjs, src/zen/common/moz.build,
# src/zen/moz.build, src/browser/base/content/zen-assets.jar.inc.mn. Applies on
# top of 0028.
